        <title>Edit multiple data sets at
            onc<?oxy_comment_start author="cecilia" timestamp="20160609T135643+0200" comment="Previous info: Have checked with SME, function should be in Maintenance app but might not be included in release 24.
- Not included in release 2.24." flag="done"?>e<?oxy_comment_end?></title>
        <?oxy_custom_end?>
        <para>With the <emphasis role="bold">Data set assignment editor</emphasis> you can add and
            remove multiple data sets to organisation units at once.</para>
        <orderedlist>
            <listitem>
                <para>Click <emphasis role="bold">Apps</emphasis> > <emphasis role="bold"
                        ><?oxy_comment_start author="cecilia" timestamp="20160609T161212+0200" comment="For SME: In which app will the Data set assignment editor be?
Maintenance" flag="done"?>Maintenance<?oxy_comment_end?></emphasis>
                    > <emphasis role="bold">Data set assignment editor</emphasis>.</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
                <para>Select an organisation unit.</para>
                <para>A table appears with data sets as columns and child organisation units as
                    rows.</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
                <para>Assign or unassign data sets by clicking the corresponding icons in the
                    table.</para>
                <para>Your changes are saved automatically.</para>
                <tip>
                    <para>If you want to assign or unassign an organisation unit to all data sets,
                        select or clear the check box next to the organisation unit.</para>
                </tip>
            </listitem>
        </orderedlist>
    </section>
